choices.text:
the idea of having children early and you can see some of them getting married, living together or just randomly having kids.

They don't understand the need for university and often end up working in shitty jobs, not turning out to be that successful and they just tell me how they wish they had listened and tried harder to be more successful.
I just ignore them.

Their favourite thing to talk about is how their children are so smart and that I should enjoy my freedom now.

Yeah I can't wait to have to wake up every morning to a crying hungry baby at 2AM and another one at 5AM who's just whining about everything and how I'll never be able to drink again for the next few years.

You know how many babies I want to have? Zero.

I don't even like kids and I know raising a kid is hard work and is extremely stressfull, I don't see how anyone could honestly like to go through that and decide they wanna have them.

Even Australians hating babies is unacceptable to these guys.

But welps. I have plenty of support from guys online and so far the majority of people agree with me listening to the Australian's opinion on babies more than their Greek cousins. 

I don't want to sound too general, but do you guys have any anecdotes about how culture influenced your baby opinions and if you're happy with it or not? 

I just wanna ignore these guys and grow up so I can joing the baby non meme crew.
